From 3899bafdf69b992e79e972a8dc0b5b986d13c6a6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: sammiler <app.evergreen055@passinbox.com>
Date: Sun, 13 Jul 2025 21:47:31 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 10/13] build: Enable compilation with MSVC on Windows

This commit introduces the necessary changes to allow the project to be compiled successfully using the Microsoft Visual C++ (MSVC) toolchain on Windows.

- Adapt CMakeLists.txt for MSVC-specific compilation paths and flags.
- Introduce compat.h to handle MSVC compatibility issues.
- Apply VS_API macro to public APIs for proper DLL export/import.
- Update FindSSE.cmake to correctly detect SSE support with MSVC.
---
